sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects a Windows program executable started from a suspicious folder
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Patrick Bareiss, Anton Kutepov, oscd.community, Nasreddine Bencherchali

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: This rule looks for csrss spawning from outside of the normal system32 path. No csrss does not exist within Syswow64.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: CSRSS.exe spawned from unusual location (possible mimicking) (via cmdline)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Monitor the creation of a new key under 'TaskCache' when a new scheduled task is registered by a process that is not svchost.exe, which is suspicious
sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Scheduled TaskCache Change by Uncommon Program

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of an executable with a system process name in folders other than the system ones (System32, SysWOW64...etc).
sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Files With System Process Name In Unsuspected Locations
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Sander Wiebing, Tim Shelton, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

match_context.values: @{EventID=1; CommandLine=C:\Windows\Sysnative\cmd.exe /C "netsh advfirewall firewall add rule name="csrss" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\rss\csrss.exe" enable=yes"; Image=C:\Windows\Sysnative\cmd.exe}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects process creation events that use the Sysnative folder (common for CobaltStrike spawns)
Detects the deletion of the "Zone.Identifier" ADS by an uncommon process. Attackers can leverage this in order to bypass security restrictions that make use of the ADS such as Microsoft Office apps.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: ADS Zone.Identifier Deleted By Uncommon Application

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the Setting of Windows Defender Exclusions
Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of the "PSScriptPolicyTest" PowerShell script by an uncommon process. This file is usually generated by Microsoft Powershell to test against Applocker.
Detects suspicious process starts on Windows systems based on keywords
Detects non-interactive PowerShell activity by looking at the "powershell" process with a non-user GUI process such as "explorer.exe" as a parent.

attributes.magic: PE32 executable (GUI) Intel 80386 Mono/.Net assembly, for MS Windows

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.
